HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 873
By Darby
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Weakley County
Sheriff's Deputy Derrick R. Bonham.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
own concerns to ensure our collective freedom and personal safety; in providing for the
domestic tranquility of the community as a whole, society recognizes the need for a system of
laws; and
WHEREAS, the enforcement of the law has been entrusted to a small number of
dedicated individuals who face daily the rigors of human conflict in protecting those whom they
so selflessly serve; and
WHEREAS, the people of Tennessee are fortunate to be served by the brave and
dedicated law enforcement officers who put their lives on the line while carrying out their
essential duties; and
WHEREAS, Deputy Derrick R. Bonham of the Weakley County Sheriff's Department was
one such outstanding and heroic public servant, who gave his life while serving his fellow
citizens on January 30, 2026; and
WHEREAS, born on December 6, 1988, Deputy Bonham was a resident of Greenfield; a
veteran of the United States Army, he graduated from the Tennessee Law Enforcement
Training Academy on December 21, 2023, and honorably served the citizens of Weakley
County with the Sheriff's Office for nearly two years; and
WHEREAS, Deputy Bonham chose a life of service in every capacity—a life rooted in
protecting and serving everyone in his community, standing strong in the face of uncertainty and
danger, and answering the call when his community needed him; and
HJR0873
012709
- 1 -

WHEREAS, his courage, humility, quiet strength, kindness, and commitment to duty
reflect the very best of humanity; and
WHEREAS, Deputy Derrick Bonham was deeply devoted to his family and always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, left to mourn his memory and carry on his legacy are his wife, Nicole
Bonham; children, Harper, Hayden, and Hudson; mother, Bertha Bonham; father, John
Bonham; brother, "John Boy" (Cynthia) Bonham; nephew and niece, Daniel and Frankie; in-
laws, Troy and BeLynda Jones; uncle, Jerry Armes; and grandmother-in-law, June Neblett; and
WHEREAS, Deputy Bonham leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity, probity, and
valor in his public life as a law enforcement officer, compassion and loyalty in private life, and
dedication in all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the too brief yet bountiful life of this
exceptional public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the life of Weakley County Sheriff's Deputy Derrick R. Bonham,
reflecting fondly upon his character and his commitment to public service.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family and friends of Deputy Bonham.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
